      'Engineered inequity': 'Robert Moses\' bridges, built low so buses could not reach the beaches, are this week\'s founding example, and they are an argument you can write about: artifacts have politics. Engineered inequity names design that encodes a social decision, and the humanities method, read the artifact as a text with an author and interests, is exactly the analysis required.',
